WEBVTT

00:01.235 --> 00:04.338
YOU KNOW THE KIND OF GUY
WHO DOES NOTHING
BUT BAD THINGS...

00:04.372 --> 00:07.175
AND THEN WONDERS WHY
HIS LIFE SUCKS?

00:07.208 --> 00:11.145
WELL, THAT WAS ME.
EVERY TIME SOMETHIN' GOOD
HAPPENED TO ME,

00:11.179 --> 00:13.281
SOMETHIN' BAD
WAS ALWAYS WAITIN'
AROUND THE CORNER.

00:15.516 --> 00:17.118
KARMA.

00:17.151 --> 00:19.220
THAT'S WHEN I REALIZED
I HAD TO CHANGE.

00:20.754 --> 00:23.424
SO I MADE A LIST
OF EVERYTHING BAD
I'VE EVER DONE,

00:23.457 --> 00:26.394
AND, ONE BY ONE,
I'M GONNA MAKE UP
FOR ALL MY MISTAKES.

00:26.427 --> 00:28.362
I'M JUST TRYIN'
TO BE A BETTER PERSON.

00:28.396 --> 00:30.764
MY NAME IS EARL.

00:32.466 --> 00:34.468
THE TOUGH THING
ABOUT HAVING A LIST...

00:34.502 --> 00:37.138
OF OVER 200 THINGS
YOU'VE DONE WRONG TO PEOPLE...

00:37.171 --> 00:40.374
IS CHOOSING WHICH ONE
YOU'RE GONNA MAKE UP FOR NEXT.

00:40.408 --> 00:42.576
SHOULD I DO NUMBER 73--

00:42.610 --> 00:45.379
ALWAYS TOOK A PENNY,
NEVER LEFT A PENNY?

00:52.553 --> 00:54.788
COUNT THAT UP AND SEE IF I'VE
GOT ANY CHANGE COMING BACK.

00:56.624 --> 00:58.826
[ Earl Narrating ]
OR SHOULD IT BE NUMBER 86--

00:58.859 --> 01:01.395
STOLE A CAR
FROM A ONE-LEGGED GIRL?

01:02.630 --> 01:05.499
YOU SAID YOU LOVED ME!

01:05.533 --> 01:07.435
[ Ricochet ]

01:11.572 --> 01:14.375
[ Earl Narrating ]
OR SHOULD I TACKLE ONE OF
THE MANY THINGS ON THE LIST...

01:14.408 --> 01:16.177
THAT INVOLVE MY EX-WIFE, JOY?

01:18.479 --> 01:22.683
I STILL CAN'T BELIEVE THAT
SON OF A BITCH WON THE LOTTERY
RIGHT AFTER I DIVORCED HIM.

01:22.716 --> 01:24.685
HALF THAT MONEY
SHOULD BE MINE.

01:24.718 --> 01:26.720
LOOK AT MY BICEP
WHEN I DO THIS.

01:26.754 --> 01:29.190
SEE HOW IT POP OUT
RIGHT THERE ON THE SIDE?

01:29.223 --> 01:31.259
THAT'S NEW.

01:31.292 --> 01:33.161
I'M GONNA GET ME THAT MONEY.

01:38.899 --> 01:41.735
- WHAT'S THIS?
- I GOT YOU SOMETHING
TO HELP YOU WITH YOUR LIST.

01:41.769 --> 01:44.672
IT'S A QUIT SMOKING TAPE.
REMEMBER NUMBER 102--

01:44.705 --> 01:47.441
HARMED AND POSSIBLY KILLED
PEOPLE WITH SECOND-HAND SMOKE.

01:49.243 --> 01:51.879
OH, YEAH. WHERE'D YOU GET IT?
IT'S GOT JELLY ON IT.

01:51.912 --> 01:55.216
I SHOWED CATALINA WHERE
THE GOOD YARD SALES ARE.

01:55.249 --> 01:58.219
I GOT A FOOT MASSAGER
FOR TWO DOLLARS.
ALL IT NEEDS IS A NEW MOTOR.

02:00.421 --> 02:02.823
[ Earl Narrating ]
EVER SINCE THE FIRST TIME
CATALINA CLEANED OUR ROOM,

02:02.856 --> 02:06.427
RANDY'S BEEN MAKING ANY EXCUSE
TO SPEND TIME WITH HER.

02:06.460 --> 02:10.198
HEY, HOW MUCH FOR THIS TAPE
THAT HELPS YOU QUIT SMOKING?

02:10.231 --> 02:12.933
[ Synthesized Voice ]
FORTY CENTS.

02:12.966 --> 02:16.837
- HOW ABOUT 25?
- THIRTY-FIVE.

02:16.870 --> 02:19.173
- THIRTY?
- THIRTY-TWO.

02:19.207 --> 02:23.311
DEAL. HEY, SAY
"LUKE, I AM YOUR FATHER."

02:23.344 --> 02:25.813
LUKE, I AM YOUR FATHER.

02:25.846 --> 02:28.249
[ Randy ]
SO, YOU GONNA QUIT?

02:28.282 --> 02:31.952
YEAH, YEAH, I AM. I JUST
WANNA FINISH THIS PACK FIRST.
I DON'T WANNA BE WASTEFUL.

02:31.985 --> 02:34.588
NUMBER 49 ON MY LIST--
I'VE BEEN WASTEFUL.

02:34.622 --> 02:36.857
SO WHAT'S NEXT
ON YOUR LIST?

02:36.890 --> 02:40.461
I DON'T KNOW. I HAVEN'T
FIGURED THAT OUT YET.
CAN I PICK ONE?

02:40.494 --> 02:42.930
YEAH. WHY NOT?
I GOTTA DO 'EM ALL ANYWAY.

02:42.963 --> 02:45.299
HOW ABOUT--
[ Vocalizing ] 112--

02:45.333 --> 02:47.901
"LET DONNY JONES SERVE JAIL
TIME FOR A CRIME I COMMITTED?"

02:47.935 --> 02:50.904
OH, MAN.
DONNY JONES.

02:54.642 --> 02:57.278
[ Earl Narrating ]
A FEW YEARS AGO,
I ROBBED A DOUGHNUT SHOP.

02:57.311 --> 02:59.780
TO BE HONEST,
I SHOULDN'T HAVE BEEN OUT,

02:59.813 --> 03:02.483
BECAUSE I HAD A PRETTY BAD COLD,
AND I COULD'VE SPREAD IT AROUND.

03:02.516 --> 03:07.255
[ Sneezes ]
UH-OH.

03:07.288 --> 03:09.923
FORTUNATELY FOR ME, THE SECURITY
CAMERA COULDN'T SEE MY FACE,

03:09.957 --> 03:13.861
AND I HAD STOLEN THIS SHIRT
FROM A FRIEND NAMED DONNY JONES.

03:13.894 --> 03:16.997
UNFORTUNATELY FOR DONNY,
HE HAD A CHECKERED PAST...

03:17.030 --> 03:19.400
AND NO ALIBI
FOR THE NIGHT OF THE ROBBERY.

03:19.433 --> 03:23.003
NUMBER FOUR, STEP FORWARD.

03:23.036 --> 03:26.774
[ Earl Narrating ]
AND MOST UNFORTUNATE FOR DONNY,
HE HAD ALSO CAUGHT MY COLD.

03:26.807 --> 03:29.277
THAT'S HIM.
NUMBER FOUR.

03:29.310 --> 03:30.978
WHAT?

03:33.414 --> 03:36.950
A JURY FOUND DONNY GUILTY, AND
HE SERVED TWO YEARS IN PRISON.

03:39.520 --> 03:41.555
I'M NOT DOING DONNY JONES.

03:41.589 --> 03:42.956
WHY NOT?
I JUST DON'T WANT TO.

03:42.990 --> 03:45.025
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHERE HE LIVES.

03:45.058 --> 03:47.995
THEY GOT BIG YELLOW BOOKS
TO FIND THAT STUFF OUT, EARL.

03:48.028 --> 03:50.898
I'LL QUIT SMOKING, ALL RIGHT?
I'LL DO THAT ONE.

03:50.931 --> 03:54.468
LOOK, I QUIT SMOKING.
YOU'RE SCARED OF DONNY JONES.

03:54.502 --> 03:57.505
- I'M NOT SCARED OF DONNY JONES.
- WHY ARE YOU SCARED
OF DONNY JONES?

03:57.538 --> 03:59.707
I'M NOT SCARED
OF DONNY JONES.

03:59.740 --> 04:01.842
[ Earl Narrating ]
THAT WAS A LIE.

04:01.875 --> 04:06.580
THERE AREN'T A LOT OF PEOPLE
ON THIS EARTH THAT
I'M AFRAID OF, BUT DONNY--

04:06.614 --> 04:08.482
WELL--

04:13.454 --> 04:15.489
OH, IT IS ON.

04:15.523 --> 04:18.025
[ Earl Narrating ]
DONNY IS CRAZY.

04:18.058 --> 04:21.662
[ Grunts ]

04:21.695 --> 04:25.466
[ Pounding Continues ]

04:25.499 --> 04:27.668
LOOK, I'D LOVE
TO TAKE CARE OF DONNY,

04:27.701 --> 04:30.371
BUT I CAN ONLY DO
ONE THING AT A TIME.

04:30.404 --> 04:33.841
I'M GONNA FOCUS
ON QUITTIN' SMOKING.

04:33.874 --> 04:36.410
[ Earl Narrating ]
I WAS GONNA FOCUS
ON QUITTIN' SMOKING,

04:36.444 --> 04:38.812
BUT IT TURNS OUT
QUITTIN' SMOKING IS STRESSFUL.

04:38.846 --> 04:41.449
AND WHEN I STRESSED OUT,
I SMOKE.
HEY, EARL.

04:41.482 --> 04:44.418
HEY, HOW'S IT GOIN'?

04:44.452 --> 04:46.854
- WE FOUND DONNY JONES.
- WHAT? WHY?

04:46.887 --> 04:49.823
IT WAS CATALINA'S IDEA.
SHE SAID YOU NEEDED A PUSH.

04:49.857 --> 04:53.961
WHEN SOMEONE'S SCARED,
THEY NEED A FRIEND TO PUSH THEM
TO OVERCOME THAT FEAR.

04:53.994 --> 04:57.064
YEAH, YOU KNOW, LIKE THROWING
SOMEBODY IN THE OCEAN
WHO'S AFRAID TO SWIM...

04:57.097 --> 04:59.433
OR PUTTIN' A SNAKE
IN A YOUNG GIRL'S BED.

04:59.467 --> 05:02.703
I DON'T NEED A PUSH.
I'M NOT SCARED, ALL RIGHT?

05:02.736 --> 05:04.905
I'M OCCUPIED.
I'M BUSY QUITTIN' SMOKING.

05:04.938 --> 05:07.741
WE'RE JUST TRYING TO HELP.

05:07.775 --> 05:10.077
[ Men Chattering, Burping ]

05:10.110 --> 05:12.380
THAT WAS THERE
WHEN I GOT HERE.

05:14.582 --> 05:19.620
QUITTIN' IS HARD, RANDY.
I DIDN'T SMOKE FOR A WHOLE HOUR,
AND I STARTED TO SHAKE.

05:19.653 --> 05:24.124
MY SYSTEM'S USED TO RUNNIN'
ON MORE TAR.

05:24.157 --> 05:26.059
[ Sighs ]

05:28.729 --> 05:33.133
[ Earl Narrating ]
I KNEW CIGARETTES COULD KILL ME,
BUT SO COULD DONNY JONES.

05:33.166 --> 05:36.537
BESIDES, AS FAR AS ME LIVIN'
A LONG LIFE WAS CONCERNED,

05:36.570 --> 05:38.672
I SHOULD HAVE BEEN MORE WORRIED
ABOUT MY EX-WIFE.

05:51.785 --> 05:54.655
OH, SNAP.

05:54.688 --> 05:58.559
DARNELL, RUN DOWN
TO THE VIDEO HUT
AND RENT ME A VCR!

06:03.196 --> 06:05.733
[ Woman ]
OH, MY GOD!
AUNT MILLIE'S WALKING!

06:05.766 --> 06:09.770
LOOK! AUNT MILLIE'S WALKING!
IT'S A MIRACLE!

06:09.803 --> 06:11.772
[ Joy On Video ]
NEXT TIME YOU STEAL A CAMERA,

06:11.805 --> 06:13.941
HAVE THE COMMON SENSE
TO STEAL THE DIRECTIONS.

06:13.974 --> 06:15.976
I THINK I GOT IT ON.
OH.

06:19.480 --> 06:23.651
[ Joy On Video ]
I LOVE YOU, EARL, AND I LOVE
ALL THIS STUFF YOU STOLE.

06:23.684 --> 06:26.720
[ Earl On Video ]
I LOVE THAT YOU LOVE ME
AND LOVE ALL THIS STUFF I STOLE.

06:26.754 --> 06:28.989
I WANT TO DOCUMENT THIS.

06:31.492 --> 06:36.830
IF I EVER DIE,
I WANT THIS WOMAN RIGHT HERE
TO HAVE EVERYTHING I OWN.

06:36.864 --> 06:38.666
EVERYTHING.

06:38.699 --> 06:42.035
OH, BABY, THAT'S SO SWEET.

06:45.038 --> 06:47.508
WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF THAT?

06:47.541 --> 06:50.578
REWIND IT. I WANNA SEE
THAT OLD LADY WALK AGAIN.

06:50.611 --> 06:52.880
[ Earl Narrating ]
JOY KNEW THAT VIDEO
WAS THE ONLY THING...

06:52.913 --> 06:55.015
CLOSE TO A WILL THAT I HAVE.

06:55.048 --> 06:57.951
NORMALLY SHE'S NOT THAT VIOLENT,
BUT MONEY MAKES PEOPLE CRAZY.

06:57.985 --> 07:00.754
I'LL TAKE THIS.

07:00.788 --> 07:02.856
THERE'S A THREE-DAY
WAITING PERIOD FOR GUNS.

07:02.890 --> 07:05.659
LAND OF THE FREE, MY ASS.

07:05.693 --> 07:08.629
FINE. WHAT CAN I
WALK OUTTA HERE WITH TODAY
THAT'LL KILL SOMEBODY?

07:08.662 --> 07:12.500
ANYTHING IN AISLE FOUR.
OH, THANK YOU.

07:12.533 --> 07:15.569
[ Earl Narrating ]
RANDY TOOK CATALINA
TO ANOTHER YARD SALE...

07:15.603 --> 07:18.071
TO LOOK FOR A MOTOR
FOR HER FOOT MASSAGER,

07:18.105 --> 07:20.908
SO I HAD SOME TIME
TO FOCUS ON QUITTIN' SMOKING.

07:22.676 --> 07:25.245
[ Man On Tape ]
I AM NOT A SMOKER.

07:25.278 --> 07:28.248
I AM NOT A SMOKER.

07:28.281 --> 07:31.251
SMOKING IS BAD.

07:31.284 --> 07:33.987
SMOKIN' IS BAD.

07:34.021 --> 07:37.124
I DON'T WANT TO DIE.

07:37.157 --> 07:39.927
I DON'T WANNA DIE.

07:41.862 --> 07:44.732
DAMN IT.

07:44.765 --> 07:48.268
- YOU, AND YOU ALONE,
ARE IN CONTROL...
- [ Horn Honks ]

07:48.301 --> 07:51.238
OF YOUR DESTINY.

07:51.271 --> 07:53.206
SHOOT.

07:55.142 --> 07:58.912
HEY, I WAS JUST LISTENING
TO YOUR TAPE. GOOD STUFF.

07:58.946 --> 08:02.215
WE GOT SOME KRAZY STRAWS
AT THE YARD SALE.

08:02.249 --> 08:05.018
WANNA GO GET
SOME SLUSH PUPPIES?
YEAH, WHY NOT?

08:05.052 --> 08:08.055
NICE, SUGARY DRINK MIGHT
GET MY MIND OFF CIGARETTES.

08:08.088 --> 08:10.624
MAN, I HOPE THESE STRAWS
DON'T HAVE THE FLU IN THEM.

08:10.658 --> 08:14.862
[ Burps ]
OH, HEY, WHOA.
WHERE'D THAT COME FROM?

08:14.895 --> 08:17.565
I HAVEN'T SMOKED ALL DAY.

08:31.344 --> 08:34.214
WHY ARE WE STOPPIN'?
I THINK WE GOT
A FLAT IN THE BACK.

08:34.247 --> 08:36.584
YEAH, I HEARD IT TOO.

08:36.617 --> 08:40.754
DAMN IT. I JUST GOT
THOSE TIRES FIVE YEARS AGO.

08:40.788 --> 08:42.756
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?

08:42.790 --> 08:45.993
- THAT'S DONNY'S HOUSE.
- WHAT?

08:46.026 --> 08:48.662
IT'S DONNY'S HOUSE.
FACE YOUR FEARS.

08:48.696 --> 08:50.998
[ Horn Honking ]

08:54.835 --> 08:57.104
THIS ISN'T FUNNY.
OPEN THE DOOR, RANDY.

08:57.137 --> 08:59.773
IT'S FOR YOUR OWN GOOD, EARL.
THIS IS YOUR SNAKE IN THE BED.

08:59.807 --> 09:01.675
I DON'T WANT
A SNAKE IN MY BED.

09:01.709 --> 09:03.811
YOU CAN'T FINISH YOUR LIST
IF YOU'RE SCARED.

09:03.844 --> 09:05.813
WE'RE DOING THIS
BECAUSE YOU'RE OUR FRIEND.

09:05.846 --> 09:08.315
- DONNY!
- STOP IT! LET ME IN!

09:09.950 --> 09:12.019
[ Horn Honks ]

09:14.287 --> 09:18.125
- [ Horn Honks ]
- RANDY, OPEN THE DOOR.

09:18.158 --> 09:22.930
EARL? EARL HICKEY?

09:28.869 --> 09:32.940
DONNY JONES!
HEY, BUDDY.

09:32.973 --> 09:36.777
[ Laughs ]
WE SHOULD, UH,
CATCH UP SOMETIME.

09:36.810 --> 09:39.012
YOU KNOW,
WHEN I DON'T HAVE TO--

09:39.046 --> 09:41.682
[ Tires Screeching ]

09:44.284 --> 09:45.786
OR NOW.

09:49.222 --> 09:51.625
[ Earl Narrating ]
HAVE YOU EVER HEARD
THE EXPRESSION "CRAZY EYES"?

09:51.659 --> 09:54.194
WELL, DONNY HAD 'EM.
EARL HICKEY.

09:54.227 --> 09:57.197
DONNY JONES.
YOU LOOK GOOD.

09:57.230 --> 09:59.900
YOU LOOK GOOD.
LOOK REAL GOOD.

09:59.933 --> 10:02.002
WHAT ARE THOSE,
NEW PANTS?

10:02.035 --> 10:04.705
NO. I HAD 'EM A WHILE.

10:04.738 --> 10:08.108
MMM, THEY STILL LOOK NEW.
NICE CREASE.

10:08.141 --> 10:10.778
I SHOULD, UH-- I SHOULD
GET ME A PAIR OF THOSE.

10:13.113 --> 10:16.950
HARD TO FIND GOOD PANTS.
[ Chuckles ]

10:16.984 --> 10:21.388
SO, YOUR BROTHER AND THAT LITTLE
MEXICAN LADY TOLD ME YOU WANTED
TO TALK TO ME ABOUT SOME LIST.

10:21.421 --> 10:25.358
DID THEY NOW?
ALL RIGHT. GOOD.

10:25.392 --> 10:27.661
YEAH, THEY CAN BE
VERY HELPFUL.

10:27.695 --> 10:31.164
[ Sighs ]
ALL RIGHT, HERE'S
THE DEAL, DONNY.

10:33.166 --> 10:37.204
I'M ON, UH,
KIND OF A MISSION.

10:37.237 --> 10:41.308
WOW, THESE ARE LONG...
AND SHARP, HUH?

10:41.341 --> 10:44.311
THEY'RE MY MOM'S.
SHE LIKES TO KNIT.

10:44.344 --> 10:48.849
GOOD FOR YOU, SWEETHEART.
NICE TO HAVE A HOBBY.

10:52.185 --> 10:54.421
ANYWAY, UH, DONNY,

10:54.454 --> 10:57.891
UM, I'VE RECENTLY
DISCOVERED KARMA,

10:57.925 --> 11:01.394
AND I'VE WRITTEN A LIST
OF ALL THE BAD THINGS
I'VE DONE IN MY LIFE,

11:01.428 --> 11:03.897
AND I'M TRYING
TO MAKE UP FOR 'EM.

11:03.931 --> 11:06.266
I THINK I KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE GETTIN' AT, EARL.

11:08.368 --> 11:10.738
YOU DO?
YEP.

11:10.771 --> 11:14.908
YOU HAD AN AWAKENING.
SAME THING HAPPENED TO ME
IN THE JOINT...

11:14.942 --> 11:17.144
WHEN I FOUND JESUS.

11:18.912 --> 11:21.882
- WOW.
- NICE, HUH?

11:21.915 --> 11:25.719
I ALSO GOT MOSES PARTIN'
THE RED SEA ON MY BOTTOM.
YOU WANNA SEE THAT?

11:25.753 --> 11:29.156
- NO, NO. M-MAYBE LATER.
- OKAY.

11:32.325 --> 11:36.029
SO, ANYWAY, ABOUT A MONTH
INTO MY SENTENCE,

11:36.063 --> 11:40.167
I STARTED READIN' THE BIBLE,
AND IT REALLY KEPT ME
OUT OF TROUBLE.

11:40.200 --> 11:42.269
[ Alarms Blaring ]
[ Men Shouting ]

11:42.302 --> 11:45.906
HEY, HEY, WE'RE GONNA
GANG-STOMP THE GUARD
IN THE CAFETERIA. YOU IN?

11:45.939 --> 11:49.076
SORRY. I'M BUSY STOMPIN'
THE DEVIL OUT OF MY HEART.

11:49.109 --> 11:51.945
BUT THANKS
FOR THINKING OF ME.

11:51.979 --> 11:55.515
EVER SINCE I FOUND THE LORD,
I REALLY TURNED MY LIFE AROUND.

11:55.548 --> 11:58.051
PRISON TURNED OUT TO BE
A BLESSING IN DISGUISE.

11:58.085 --> 12:02.956
SO... YOU'RE NOT MAD
THAT YOU WERE MISTAKENLY
INCARCERATED...

12:02.990 --> 12:07.194
FOR A CRIME SOME...
UNKNOWN PERSON COMMITTED?

12:07.227 --> 12:10.097
I DIDN'T ROB THAT STORE, EARL,
BUT WE BOTH KNOW I WAS A SINNER.

12:10.130 --> 12:14.401
BESIDES, AS THE GOOD BOOK SAYS,

12:14.434 --> 12:17.204
FORGIVENESS IS THE WAY
TO SALVATION.

12:17.237 --> 12:19.206
[ Grunts ]
[ Cushion Deflating ]

12:20.573 --> 12:22.776
WOW. THAT'S A BIG BIBLE.

12:22.810 --> 12:25.278
IT'S MY MOM'S.
LARGE PRINT.

12:25.312 --> 12:28.381
- AH.
- SHE REFUSES TO WEAR
HER READIN' GLASSES.

12:28.415 --> 12:31.351
[ Whispering ]
SHE THINKS THEY
MAKE HER LOOK OLD.

12:34.521 --> 12:37.925
"DO NOT DRINK WINE WHEN...

12:40.593 --> 12:43.496
"THOU GOEST INTO THE TABER--

12:46.399 --> 12:48.869
NACLE OF THE LORD."

12:52.005 --> 12:55.242
SO, YOU'RE ALL CHURCHED UP
THEN, HUH? GOOD FOR YOU.

12:55.275 --> 12:58.211
GIVIN' UP ALL THAT
HURTIN' PEOPLE.

12:58.245 --> 13:01.815
I TURN THE OTHER CHEEK NOW.
AND YOU GOT A TATTOO
OF THE RED SEA TO PROVE IT.

13:01.849 --> 13:04.184
- WANNA SEE IT NOW?
- OOH, NOT--

13:04.217 --> 13:06.186
I'M STILL
GONNA PASS ON THAT.

13:06.219 --> 13:08.856
BUT I DO NEED
TO TELL YOU SOMETHING.

13:08.889 --> 13:13.260
UH, SOMETHING I DID TO YOU
THAT'S ON MY LIST.

13:13.293 --> 13:16.997
SOMETHING THAT TURNED OUT
TO BE GOOD FOR YOU
BUT, ALL THE SAME,

13:17.030 --> 13:19.399
SOMETHING THAT WAS WRONG.

13:22.936 --> 13:25.438
I WAS THE ONE THAT, UH,
ROBBED THAT DOUGHNUT STORE.

13:27.540 --> 13:30.944
- WHAT?
- IT WAS ME, DONNY.

13:30.978 --> 13:34.948
I WAS WEARING A-- A SHIRT
THAT I STOLE FROM YOU.

13:34.982 --> 13:37.617
I-- I'M THE REASON
YOU WENT TO PRISON.

13:37.650 --> 13:39.887
[ Hits Table ]

13:45.525 --> 13:48.295
THEN FOUND THE LORD.

13:48.328 --> 13:50.563
WENT TO PRISON
AND FOUND THE LORD.

13:52.599 --> 13:55.903
[ Earl Narrating ]
EVEN THOUGH DONNY HAD CHANGED,
I WAS STILL SCARED,

13:55.936 --> 13:58.371
'CAUSE NO MATTER
WHO HE WAS NOW--

13:58.405 --> 14:01.474
[ Laughing ]
I GOT YOUR GUN.

14:01.508 --> 14:04.011
I GOT YOUR GUN, DUMMY.
I GOT YOUR GUN.

14:04.044 --> 14:06.246
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?
[ Laughing Continues ]

14:06.279 --> 14:08.048
[ Earl Narrating ]
DONNY USED TO BE CRAZY.

14:15.522 --> 14:17.857
[ Whispering ]
WHAT WOULD JESUS DO?

14:28.635 --> 14:30.470
[ Whispering ]
WHAT WOULD YOU DO?

14:32.205 --> 14:34.074
OKAY.

14:38.178 --> 14:42.382
- I FORGIVE YOU.
- REALLY?

14:42.415 --> 14:46.987
LIKE I SAID BEFORE, EARL,
PRISON CHANGED MY LIFE.

14:47.020 --> 14:50.323
I MEAN, EVEN IF YOU HADN'T
HAVE DONE WHAT YOU DID,

14:50.357 --> 14:52.960
I PROBABLY WOULD'VE
ENDED UP THERE ANYWAY.

14:52.993 --> 14:56.096
CROSS ME OFF YOUR LIST.

14:56.129 --> 14:59.299
ALL RIGHT. THANK YOU.

14:59.332 --> 15:02.502
I WILL.
THANKS, DONNY.

15:02.535 --> 15:06.506
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
I GOTTA GO HELP A PRAYER BUDDY
IN THE GARAGE.

15:06.539 --> 15:10.643
WHEN HE SHOWED UP, I THOUGHT
HE WAS SPEAKING IN TONGUES, BUT
HE'S JUST BACK ON THE STUFF.

15:10.677 --> 15:13.280
HEY, DON'T WORRY.
I'LL LET MYSELF OUT.

15:13.313 --> 15:15.382
[ Earl Narrating ]
AND THERE IT WAS--

15:15.415 --> 15:17.684
THANKS TO RANDY
AND CATALINA'S PUSH,

15:17.717 --> 15:20.620
I FACED MY FEARS,
AND EVERYTHING TURNED OUT FINE.

15:28.128 --> 15:30.197
OW! WHAT THE HELL?

15:30.230 --> 15:32.632
YOU PUT MY BABY IN PRISON
FOR TWO YEARS!

15:32.665 --> 15:34.601
TAKE IT EASY!
HE FORGAVE ME!

15:34.634 --> 15:37.270
WELL, MAYBE HE FORGAVE YOU,
BUT I DON'T!

15:40.673 --> 15:44.377
[ Screams ]
HELP! HELP!

15:44.411 --> 15:49.149
YOU TOOK MY BABY AWAY!
I'LL NEVER GET THOSE YEARS BACK!
I SHOULD BE ON YOUR STUPID LIST!

15:49.182 --> 15:53.620
[ Screams ]
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY. OKAY.
I'LL PUT YOU ON.

15:53.653 --> 15:59.292
TOOK DONNY AWAY FROM HIS MOTHER
FOR TWO YEARS.

15:59.326 --> 16:03.396
ALL RIGHT. YOU'RE ON IT.
NOW WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO
TO GET YOU OFF IT?

16:03.430 --> 16:06.499
- GET ME THE TWO YEARS BACK.
- YOU KNOW I CAN'T DO THAT.

16:06.533 --> 16:08.735
AW, I GUESS YOU'RE SCREWED.

16:08.768 --> 16:12.172
[ Grunts, Groans ]

16:42.735 --> 16:46.039
[ Muffled Shouting ]

16:46.073 --> 16:49.142
[ Earl Narrating ]
I KNOW THIS LOOKS BAD, BUT
SHE REFUSED TO COME ON HER OWN.

16:49.176 --> 16:51.344
TRUST ME.
I HAVE A PLAN.
HI, EARL.

16:51.378 --> 16:53.346
HEY, CRAB MAN.
[ Shouting ]

16:53.380 --> 16:57.184
- JOY WANTED ME TO BRING YOU
THESE POISON COOKIES.
- HUH?

16:57.217 --> 16:59.752
[ Earl Narrating ]
DARNELL FILLED ME IN
ON THE VIDEO WILL...

16:59.786 --> 17:02.089
AND JOY'S INTENT TO KILL ME.

17:04.624 --> 17:08.195
I WASN'T GONNA GET INVOLVED,
BUT NOW SHE GOT ME
DELIVERIN' POISON,

17:08.228 --> 17:10.697
IT JUST DON'T SEEM RIGHT.

17:10.730 --> 17:14.734
- THANKS, CRAB MAN.
- NO PROBLEM, EARL.

17:14.767 --> 17:17.837
[ Muffled Shouting ]

17:17.870 --> 17:20.307
LET ME OUT OF HERE
RIGHT NOW!

17:20.340 --> 17:23.176
YOU LET ME OUT OF HERE!

17:23.210 --> 17:26.279
EARL, HOW COME YOU'RE TAPING
DONNY'S MOM TO A CHAIR?

17:26.313 --> 17:29.082
- OOH, COOKIES.
- RANDY, THOSE ARE POISONED.

17:29.116 --> 17:31.684
OH, OKAY.

17:31.718 --> 17:35.288
I'M TAPING HER TO THE CHAIR
BECAUSE SHE'S GONNA QUIT SMOKING
BEFORE IT KILLS HER.

17:35.322 --> 17:38.658
- NOW, STOP KICKING.
- SOMETHING ABOUT THIS
FEELS WRONG.

17:38.691 --> 17:41.661
NO, IT'S FINE.
I'M GIVING HER A PUSH,

17:41.694 --> 17:44.431
JUST LIKE YOU GUYS
GAVE ME A PUSH.

17:44.464 --> 17:47.467
[ Horn Honking ]
I HAVE TO DO THIS.
YOU'RE ON MY LIST NOW.

17:47.500 --> 17:49.769
I TOOK YOUR SON
AWAY FROM YOU FOR TWO YEARS,

17:49.802 --> 17:52.439
AND THE ONLY WAY I CAN
GIVE YOU BACK THAT TIME...

17:52.472 --> 17:55.142
IS TO GIVE YOU
TWO MORE YEARS ON THIS EARTH.

17:55.175 --> 17:58.811
RANDY--
THOSE ARE POISON!

18:01.714 --> 18:04.717
- HOW POISON?
- PUT IT DOWN!

18:04.751 --> 18:07.520
LOOK, I KNOW
IT'S NOT GONNA BE EASY,

18:07.554 --> 18:09.622
BUT YOU'RE NOT
GONNA DO IT ALONE.

18:09.656 --> 18:12.292
I'M GONNA QUIT WITH YOU.

18:14.227 --> 18:16.496
I KNOW YOU'RE SCARED
TO GIVE UP THE SMOKES.

18:16.529 --> 18:19.832
SO AM I. WE'RE GONNA
GET THROUGH THIS TOGETHER.

18:19.866 --> 18:22.735
THIS IS THE SWEETEST,
MOST JUSTIFIED KIDNAPPING
I'VE EVER SEEN.

18:22.769 --> 18:25.305
- HOW MANY HAVE YOU SEEN?
- FIVE OR SO.

18:27.240 --> 18:29.776
I'M GONNA TAKE THE GAG
OUT OF YOUR MOUTH NOW, OKAY?

18:29.809 --> 18:31.778
SO PLEASE DON'T HOLLER.
[ Mutters ]

18:31.811 --> 18:33.880
HEL--
[ Coughing ]

18:33.913 --> 18:35.915
HEL--
[ Coughing ]

18:35.948 --> 18:39.319
[ Coughing Continues ]

18:39.352 --> 18:41.854
HELP!

18:44.924 --> 18:47.627
HEL--

18:47.660 --> 18:50.730
[ Gasping ]

18:53.400 --> 18:55.535
[ Earl Narrating ]
TURNS OUT I DIDN'T NEED THE GAG.

18:55.568 --> 18:58.471
FORTY YEARS OF SMOKING HAD TAKEN
AWAY HER ABILITY TO SCREAM.

18:58.505 --> 19:01.441
ALL RIGHT, FINE.
I'LL QUIT.

19:01.474 --> 19:03.476
THAT'S MY GIRL.

19:06.913 --> 19:09.682
[ Earl Narrating ]
QUITTIN' SMOKING
IS A LOT LIKE PRISON.

19:09.716 --> 19:12.885
IF YOU CAN GET
THROUGH THE FIRST THREE DAYS,
YOU'VE GOT A FIGHTING CHANCE.

19:19.592 --> 19:21.761
FIRST WE TRIED THE TAPES.

19:21.794 --> 19:24.431
[ Man On Tape ]
I DON'T WANT TO DIE.

19:24.464 --> 19:27.500
I DON'T WANT TO DIE.
I DON'T WANT TO DIE.

19:29.702 --> 19:31.504
[ Earl Narrating ]
THEN WE TRIED THE PATCHES.

19:36.976 --> 19:40.347
SOMEONE TOLD US TO TRY
CARROT STICKS AS A SUBSTITUTE,

19:40.380 --> 19:42.382
BUT WE COULDN'T GET
THE DAMN THINGS TO LIGHT.

19:52.292 --> 19:56.896
AFTER SOME LAUGHTER, SOME TEARS
AND A LOT OF BURNT CARROTS,

19:56.929 --> 19:58.931
TOGETHER WE BATTLED
OUR ADDICTION, AND WE WON.

20:11.811 --> 20:14.847
AND EVEN THOUGH WE STARTED OUT
AS STRANGERS, BY THE END,

20:14.881 --> 20:17.917
I FELT LIKE I KNEW DONNY'S MOM
AS WELL AS I KNEW MY OWN.

20:17.950 --> 20:22.422
THANK YOU, EARL.
THANK YOU...
DONNY'S MOM.

20:30.830 --> 20:33.300
[ Earl Narrating ]
IT WAS HARD,
BUT IT WAS WORTH IT.

20:33.333 --> 20:35.702
WE GAVE EACH OTHER LIFE.

20:35.735 --> 20:39.372
SHE'S GONNA GET THOSE
EXTRA YEARS WITH HER SON
THAT SHE WANTED,

20:39.406 --> 20:41.841
AND I JUST MIGHT GET
A FEW EXTRA YEARS MYSELF.

20:41.874 --> 20:44.577
IT'S HARD TO BELIEVE WE GOT ALL
THAT IN JUST THREE LITTLE DAYS.

20:49.015 --> 20:52.619
UNFORTUNATELY,
THERE ARE OTHER THINGS
A PERSON CAN GET IN THREE DAYS.

20:54.854 --> 20:59.526
I WROTE UP A NEW WILL, JOY.
YOU CAN KILL ME, BUT
THERE AIN'T NO MONEY IN IT.

20:59.559 --> 21:01.461
[ Sighs ]
